{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17598195","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17598195"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:34:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:34:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15447"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15447","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15447"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.28,0.41,0.17,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8138"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116600"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8138","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8138"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15447"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98593"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"},{"type":"tags","id":"8137"},{"type":"tags","id":"8741"},{"type":"tags","id":"9507"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19724"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19726"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116600","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/116600"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA patient has been diagnosed with a carcinoma of the descending colon. The disease has been staged with the TNM system where:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ET - primary tumour\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EN - node\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EM - metastasis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENo evidence is found on CT scanning of any spread to local lymph nodes or distal sites. A formal histological assessment has shown that the tumour has spread into the pericolic fat.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following T stages corresponds to this tumour?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["T1","T2","T3","T4a","T4b"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe T staging of colorectal cancer is determined by the extent of tumour invasion through the bowel wall layers. In this case, the tumour has invaded into the pericolic fat, which corresponds to \u003Cstrong\u003ET3\u003C/strong\u003E staging - infiltration into subserosa or pericolic tissue.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ET1\u003C/strong\u003E represents infiltration into submucosa only, which is much more superficial than the invasion described in this case. \u003Cstrong\u003ET2\u003C/strong\u003E indicates infiltration into muscularis propria, which again represents less extensive invasion than what has occurred here. \u003Cstrong\u003ET4a\u003C/strong\u003E would require infiltration of the serosa (visceral peritoneum), which has not been described, while \u003Cstrong\u003ET4b\u003C/strong\u003E represents the most advanced local stage with infiltration of adjacent tissues or organs, which is beyond what is present in this scenario.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EApplying the TNM classification, this patient has T3 N0 M0 disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Colorectal cancer staging is based on the depth of tumour invasion and spread to lymph nodes and distant sites.","T3 stage in colorectal cancer indicates tumour invasion into perirectal fat but not beyond the visceral peritoneum or into adjacent organs."],"references":["IARC Working Group on the Evaluation of Cancer-Preventive Interventions. Colorectal cancer screening. Lyon (FR): International Agency for Research on Cancer; 2019. 1. COLORECTAL CANCER. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK553197/","Puppa G, Sonzogni A, Colombari R, Pelosi G. TNM staging system of colorectal carcinoma: a critical appraisal of challenging issues. Arch Pathol Lab Med. 2010 Jun;134(6):837-52. doi: 10.5858/134.6.837. PMID: 20524862.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Brenner H, Kloor M, Pox CP. Colorectal cancer. Lancet 2014; 383: 1490\u2013502"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98593"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15447"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98593","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/98593"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-30T05:29:04+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-30T05:29:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8138"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116600"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https:/